item.title: How Can I Add Objects Ingame?
item.dc:creator: @guthan38 guthan38
item.description:
@guthan38 wrote:

No. When you put the object into the public void NewObjects(), you would put it in like this:

AddGlobalObject(3563, 3321, 2213, 0, 10);//booth

3563, 3321 being the coordiantes—>2213 being the object—>0 being the height—>10 being what it is, for example a roof.

item.title: How Can I Add Objects Ingame?
item.dc:creator: @guthan38 guthan38
item.description:
@guthan38 wrote:

Add fedexers stuff—>Make sure you have the newobjects void(doesn’t really matter just have a void with objects in it). DO NOT call the void under boolean process. Make a command like:

else if (command.startsWith("objects")) { NewObjects(); }

This will spawn the objects without anything lag.
